📘 Document Setup Manual
Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System
1. Purpose

This document defines the setup, configuration, and operational guidelines for implementing an automated onboarding and offboarding system that integrates HR, IT, and compliance workflows.

2. Scope

This manual covers:

System configuration
Workflow setup
Role definitions
Document templates
Integration setup
Security and compliance configuration
3. Prerequisites

Before setup, ensure:

HR system is defined (e.g., employee master database)
IT systems for provisioning are identified
Email/communication system is active
Access to IAM (Identity & Access Management)
Admin credentials for all integrated systems
4. System Components Setup
4.1 HR System Integration

Configure employee data source:

Employee ID (unique key)
Name, department, designation
Reporting manager
Joining & exit dates

Setup Steps:

Connect HR database/API
Map employee fields
Enable real-time sync or scheduled sync
Validate data flow
4.2 Identity & Access Management (IAM)

Configure account provisioning:

Email creation rules
Role-based access policies
Group assignments

Setup Steps:

Connect IAM provider (LDAP / Azure AD / Google Workspace)
Define role-to-access mapping
Configure auto provisioning triggers
Enable de-provisioning on exit event
4.3 Workflow Engine Setup

Define onboarding and offboarding workflows:

Onboarding Workflow includes:

HR verification
IT account creation
Asset allocation
Training assignment
Manager approval

Offboarding Workflow includes:

Access revocation
Asset return tracking
Payroll finalization
Compliance checklist

Setup Steps:

Create workflow templates
Define triggers (JOINED / EXITED)
Assign tasks to departments
Configure SLA timelines
4.4 Communication Setup

Configure notification channels:

Email alerts
Slack / Teams messages
Dashboard notifications

Setup Steps:

Connect email server (SMTP/API)
Integrate chat tools
Define message templates
Enable event-based notifications
4.5 Document Management Setup

Manage employee documents:

Offer letter
NDA agreements
Policy acknowledgment
Exit clearance forms

Setup Steps:

Define document templates
Enable e-signature integration (if applicable)
Set storage location (cloud/local)
Configure retention policies
4.6 ITSM Integration (Optional)

For ticket automation:

Hardware provisioning tickets
Access request tickets
Exit clearance tickets

Setup Steps:

Connect ITSM tool
Map workflow events to tickets
Assign auto-routing rules
Enable ticket status sync
5. Role Configuration

Define system roles:

Role	Responsibility
HR Admin	Employee lifecycle management
IT Admin	Account & access provisioning
Manager	Task approvals & onboarding support
Finance	Payroll & settlement
Employee	Self-service portal access
6. Workflow Triggers
Event	Trigger Action
New Hire Created	Start onboarding workflow
Employee Active	Grant system access
Exit Approved	Start offboarding workflow
Exit Completed	Revoke all access
7. Security Configuration
Enable role-based access control (RBAC)
Enable audit logging
Enforce MFA for admin users
Encrypt employee data at rest and in transit
Set access expiry for temporary roles
8. Testing Procedure
Onboarding Test:
Create dummy employee
Verify account creation
Check task assignment
Validate notifications
Offboarding Test:
Trigger exit event
Confirm access revocation
Validate asset checklist completion
Check audit logs
9. Deployment Steps
Configure environment (dev → staging → production)
Run integration tests
Validate workflows
Enable monitoring
Go live
10. Maintenance Guidelines
Review workflows quarterly
Update role access regularly
Audit logs monthly
Remove inactive integrations
Update document templates as policies change
11. Troubleshooting
Issue	Cause	Solution
Account not created	IAM sync failure	Check API connection
Workflow not triggered	Missing event mapping	Verify trigger rules
Email not sent	SMTP issue	Check server config
Task not assigned	Role mismatch	Update role mapping
